  "title": "Senior Systems Engineer – Windows & Linux",
  "description": "<h3>Role Summary</h3><p>We are looking for an experienced <strong>OS Subject Matter Expert (L3)</strong> to provide advanced support and expertise across Windows and RHEL environments. The role involves deep-level troubleshooting, clustering support, and scripting to ensure stability, performance, and availability of critical systems.</p><h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Provide <strong>L3 support</strong> for Windows and RHEL operating systems in production environments</p></li><li><p>Perform advanced troubleshooting, root cause analysis, and issue resolution</p></li><li><p>Manage and support <strong>Windows and Linux clustering</strong> environments</p></li><li><p>Develop and maintain scripts for automation and operational efficiency</p></li><li><p>Work closely with cross-functional teams to resolve complex OS-related issues</p></li><li><p>Support system availability, performance tuning, and patching activities</p></li></ul><h3>Required Skills</h3><p><strong>Windows:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Strong hands-on experience with Windows Server</p></li><li><p>PowerShell scripting</p></li><li><p>WMI</p></li><li><p>Windows Failover Clustering</p></li></ul><p><strong>RHEL:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Strong experience with Red Hat Enterprise Linux</p></li><li><p>Shell scripting (Bash)</p></li><li><p>Linux clustering experience</p></li></ul><h3>Nice to Have</h3><ul><li><p>Exposure to enterprise infrastructure or platform environments</p></li><li><p>Experience supporting large-scale or mission-critical systems</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with automation and operational best practices</p></li></ul><h3>Profile</h3><ul><li><p>Proven experience operating at <strong>L3 / SME level</strong></p></li><li><p>Strong problem-solving and analytical skills</p></li><li><p>Ability to work independently in high-pressure environments<br /></p><p>#OSSME #L3Support #WindowsServer #RHEL #PowerShell #Linux #SystemsEngineer #Infrastructure</p></li></ul>",
